column70: STEWARDSHIP SCIENCE GRANT PROGRAM
column73:
CENTER FOR MATTER UNDER EXTREME CONDITIONS (CMEC). 
THE PROPOSED CENTER FOR MATTER UNDER EXTREME CONDITIONS (CMEC) WILL ADDRESS COMPLEX ISSUES IN THREE AREAS OF RESEARCH: I) ENERGY TRANSPORT IN HED SYSTEMS (CONDUCTIVITY, SPECIES SEPARATION, LASER PLASMA INSTABILITIES, AND OPACITY), INCLUDING THE EFFECT OF EXTERNAL MAGNETIC FIELDS; II) MATERIAL PROPERTIES ACROSS THE HED REGIME (ELECTRICAL AND THERMAL CONDUCTIVITY, EQUATION OF STATE, STRUCTURE, STRENGTH, AND PHASE SEPARATION); AND III) NATURE UNDER EXTREME CONDITIONS (BROAD EQUATION OF STATE MODELS FOR PLANETARY AND ASTROPHYSICAL APPLICATIONS, AND PARTICLE ACCELERATION IN COLLISIONLESS SHOCKS). RESEARCH IN THE AREA OF DIAGNOSTICS, SPECIFICALLY SPECTROSCOPY TECHNIQUES WILL BE CONDUCTED. THESE TOPICS ARE ESSENTIAL TO THE STOCKPILE STEWARDSHIP PROGRAM (SSP).
THE CMEC WILL ENABLE SCIENTISTS AT THE PARTNER INSTITUTIONS AND NNSA NATIONAL LABORATORIES TO LEAD COLLABORATIVE RESEARCH AND TO MAKE TECHNOLOGICAL BREAKTHROUGHS IN HEDP. RESEARCH WILL FOCUS ON THE CREATION AND DIAGNOSIS OF EXTREME STATES OF MATTER, BOTH UN-MAGNETIZED AND MAGNETIZED, EXPLOITING NOVEL COMBINATIONS OF HED DRIVERS TO TRAIN FUTURE SCIENTISTS, USING BOTH MODELING AND EXPERIMENTS TO DEVELOP A PHYSICS UNDERSTANDING OF HED SYSTEMS.

THE OFFICE OF ENERGY EFFICIENCY AND RENEWABLE ENERGY IS ISSUING, ON BEHALF OF THE VEHICLE TECHNOLOGIES OFFICE, A FUNDING OPPORTUNITY ANNOUNCEMENT ENTITLED, FISCAL YEAR 2020 ADVANCED VEHICLE TECHNOLOGIES RESEARCH FUNDING OPPORTUNITY ANNOUNCEMENT.

THIS ANNOUNCEMENT SEEKS RESEARCH PROJECTS TO ADDRESS PRIORITIES IN THE FOLLOWING AREAS: ADVANCED BATTERIES AND ELECTRIFICATION IN SUPPORT OF THE RECENTLY-ANNOUNCED DOE ENERGY STORAGE GRAND CHALLENGE; ADVANCED ENGINE AND FUEL TECHNOLOGIES, INCLUDING TECHNOLOGIES FOR OFF-ROAD APPLICATIONS AND ALTERNATIVE FUELED ENGINES; LIGHTWEIGHT MATERIALS; NEW MOBILITY TECHNOLOGIES (ENERGY EFFICIENT MOBILITY SYSTEMS); AND ALTERNATIVE FUELS TECHNOLOGY DEMONSTRATIONS.

column73:
OPUS 12, INC.:  NEW SCALEUP FIXED-AMOUNT GRANT.

CONTROL NUMBER: 2166-1530
TITLE: “PEM CO2 ELECTROLYZER SCALE-UP”

OPUS 12 PROPOSES TO BUILD A >100 CELL STACK OF >1,500 CM2 ELECTRODE AREA MEMBRANE-ELECTRODE ASSEMBLIES (MEAS) BASED ON THE EXISTING MW-SCALE PEM WATER ELECTROLYZER DESIGN OF OPUS 12’S MANUFACTURING PARTNER, NEL HYDROGEN. PERFORMER WILL DEMONSTRATE THE SYSTEM ONSITE USING CO2 EMISSIONS FROM A STEAM METHANE REFORMER (SMR) OPERATED BY COMMERCIALIZATION PARTNER, SOCALGAS, THE LARGEST NATURAL GAS UTILITY IN THE US. THE SYSTEM WOULD GENERATE OVER 500 KG/DAY OF CO. THIS SYSTEM WOULD BE THE LARGEST CO2 ELECTROLYZER BUILT TO DATE AND WOULD BE A MAJOR MILESTONE IN DEMONSTRATING THAT THE TECHNOLOGY CAN MEET THE NEEDS OF THE CHEMICAL AND ENERGY INDUSTRIES.

column70: STEWARDSHIP SCIENCE GRANT PROGRAM
column73:
THIS ACADEMIC-LED PROPOSAL COMPRISES EXPERTISE IN MAGNETIZED HIGH ENERGY DENSITY (HED) PHYSICS AND SPECTROSCOPY FROM UC SAN DIEGO, UN RENO, SNL, LLE, UR, UNIV. BORDEAUX, IMPERIAL COLLEGE LONDON, AND UNIV. LAS PALMAS DE GRAN CANARIA. WE PROPOSE TO USE THE OMEGA FACILITY FOR A BASIC RESEARCH INVESTIGATION INTO THE PLASMA DYNAMICS OF MAGNETIZED CYLINDRICAL IMPLOSIONS WITH A SEED B-FIELD OF AT LEAST 50 T GENERATED BY LASER-DRIVEN CAPACITOR-COIL TARGETS (CCT).

THE LAYOUT OF OUR EXPERIMENTAL APPROACH IS SHOWN IN THE FIGURE. A 20 ΜM-THICK, 300 ΜM-RADIUS PLASTIC CYLINDER FILLED WITH DEUTERIUM-GAS AT 11 ATM PRESSURE (IN LINE WITH RECENT MINI-MAGLIF OMEGA EXPERIMENTS) WILL BE IMPLODED BY 40 OMEGA LONG PULSE LASERS (15 KJ IN UV), WITH THE SEED B-FIELD AND WITHOUT IT, FOR REFERENCE. THE SEED WILL BE GENERATED BY TWO CCTS, CCTS.

THE D2 WILL BE DOPED WITH ARGON IN ORDER TO USE THE WELL-CHARACTERIZED K-SHELL X-RAY LINE EMISSION THROUGHOUT THE COLLAPSE OF THE IMPLOSION AND AT STAGNATION TO EXTRACT PLASMA CONDITIONS. THE KSHELL SPECTRUM IS SENSITIVE TO PLASMA CONDITIONS THROUGH THE TEMPERATURE AND DENSITY SENSITIVITY OF THE ATOMIC LEVEL POPULATION KINETICS AND THE DENSITY DEPENDENCE OF THE STARK-BROADENED LINE SHAPES. SPECTRA WILL BE COMPARED FOR SHOTS WITH AND WITHOUT THE SEED B-FIELD. THE EXPERIMENTAL OBSERVATIONS WILL BE COMPARED TO FLASH AND GORGON MHD SIMULATIONS, COUPLED TO STATE-OF-THE-ART CALCULATIONS OF ATOMIC EMISSION LINE SHAPE, MOLECULAR DYNAMICS AND RADIATION TRANSPORT THROUGH THE IMPLODED PLASMAS. PRELIMINARY MAGNETO-HYDRODYNAMIC (MHD) SIMULATIONS PREDICT CORE MAGNETIZATIONS TO WELL ABOVE 10 KT.

THE DEVELOPED PLATFORM WILL SIGNIFICANTLY EXTEND THE RANGE OF ACHIEVABLE MAGNETIZATION LEVELS, ENABLING OTHER EXPERIMENTS AT THE FACILITY TO STUDY EFFECTS OF STRONG MAGNET FIELDS IN HED EXPERIMENTS. ADDITIONALLY, THE WORK WILL OPEN THE POSSIBILITY TO BENCHMARK THE NUMERICAL TOOLS AND IN PARTICULAR IMPROVE THEIR PREDICTABILITY IN TERMS OF THE NON-LOCAL B-FIELD TRANSPORT WITH THE HEAT FLOW (NERNST EFFECT) AND THERMAL TRANSPORT NORMAL TO THE TEMPERATURE GRADIENT (RIGHI-LEDUC EFFECT). NOTABLE IMPACTS OF BENCHMARKING THE VALIDITY OF MAGNETOHYDRODYNAMIC MODELING WILL BE TO ADVANCE THE MAGNETIZED LINER INERTIAL FUSION (MAGLIF) ADVANCED FUSION SCHEME AND OTHER 
APPLICATIONS SUCH AS LABORATORY-BASED ASTROPHYSICAL JETS.

THE PROPOSED WORK INVOLVES BASIC LASER–MATTER INTERACTION, AND HIGH ENERGY DENSITY PHYSICS AND HAS POTENTIAL IMPLICATIONS FOR INERTIAL CONFINEMENT FUSION. THE COLLABORATION WILL BENEFIT A NUMBER OF EARLY-CAREER SCIENTISTS INVOLVED IN THE WORK (TWO GRADUATE STUDENTS AND FOUR POSTDOCS) AND CONTRIBUTE TO THE COMMUNITY EDUCATED IN SCIENCE RELEVANT TO STOCKPILE STEWARDSHIP. THUS, THE PROJECT WILL HELP FULFILL BOTH NLUF PROGRAM OBJECTIVES. THE PROPOSED 
EXPERIMENTS ADDRESS BASIC SCIENCE ISSUES IN THE TECHNICAL SCOPE AND TOPICAL RESEARCH AREAS DEFINED IN THE NLUF FUNDING OPPORTUNITY ANNOUNCEMENT MAGNETIZED HIGH ENERGY DENSITY PLASMAS AND ALSO CONSTITUTES DIAGNOSTIC AND EXPERIMENTAL PLATFORM DEVELOPMENT.

column73:
OTHERLAB- BASE AWARD	

CONTROL #1954-1586
PROJECT TITLE: SEASTAR: SELECTIVE THALASSIC AMBULATORY RETRIEVER (STAR)

THE RECIPIENT PROPOSES TO DEVELOP A NODULE COLLECTOR CALLED THE SEASTAR, A LARGE PLATFORM ATTACHED TO A VACUUM FUNNEL THAT’S RINGED BY ROBOT ARMS. GROWTH, ELECTRIFICATION, AND INCREASED INSTALLATION OF RENEWABLE ENERGY IS DRIVING SIGNIFICANT INCREASES IN WORLDWIDE DEMAND FOR METALS LIKE MANGANESE, NICKEL, COPPER, AND COBALT. THIS INCREASE IN COMMODITY PRICES AND PROJECTED DEMAND HAS DRIVEN INTEREST IN EXPLORING NEW SOURCES OF MINERALS SUCH AS DEEP SEA MINING. THE ABYSSAL PLAIN CONTAINS LOCATIONS OF CONCENTRATED DEPOSITS OF POLYMETALLIC NODULES, 3-20CM DIAMETER METALLIC SECRETIONS WHICH ARE A YET-UNTAPPED RESERVE OF RELEVANT MINERALS THAT ARE 6KM UNDERWATER.

LELAND STANFORD JUNIOR UNIVERSITY WITH SANDIA NATIONAL LABORATORY AND NAVAL RESEARCH - BP 2 AUTHORIZATION.

CONTROL NUMBER: 1858-1794

TITLE: ''20 KV GALLIUM NITRIDE PN DIODE ELECTRO-MAGNETIC PULSE ARRESTOR FOR GRID RELIABILITY''

THE LELAND STANFORD JUNIOR UNIVERSITY, ALONG WITH SANDIA NATIONAL LABORATORIES AND NAVAL RESEARCH LABORATORY, WILL DESIGN A NEW TYPE OF EMP ARRESTOR BASED ON THE WIDE-BANDGAP SEMICONDUCTOR GALLIUM NITRIDE. THIS MATERIAL, WHICH IS ALREADY WIDELY DEPLOYED COMMERCIALLY IN AREAS SUCH AS LED-BASED SOLID-STATE LIGHTING, WILL BE USED TO FABRICATE AN EMP ARRESTOR THAT CAN RESPOND ON THE NANOSECOND TIMESCALE REQUIRED TO PROTECT AGAINST ALL EMP EVENTS.
